Package com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui

Class UIPageHandler

java.lang.Object
com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.UIPageHandler
public class UIPageHandler extends Object
Contains and handles all pages for a UINode.

  • Property Details

    • coverPage

      public javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<UIPage<?>> coverPageProperty
      Returns the cover page property for this UIPageHandler.

      The cover page is displayed when no additional pages have been added to this UIPageHandler (specifically, when the page list is empty).

      See Also:
      getCoverPage(), setCoverPage(UIPage)

  • Constructor Details

    • UIPageHandler

      public UIPageHandler​(ReentrantLock lock, UINode owner, UIPage<?> coverPage)
      Creates a new UIPageHandler with the specified owner and cover page, using the specified lock for synchronization.
      Parameters:
      lock - The ReentrantLock to be used for synchronization. Specify null for no synchronization.
      Typically the same lock used by the owner.
      owner - The UINode in which this UIPageHandler belongs to.
      coverPage - The UIPage to be displayed as the cover page. See coverPageProperty() for details.

    • getPages

      public ObservableLinkedList<UIPage<?>> getPages()
      Returns the list of pages that represent this UIPageHandler. Does not include the cover page.

      The last element of the page list is the page to be displayed by this UIPageHandler. If the page list is empty, the cover page is displayed instead.

      Returns:
      All pages that are part of this UIPageHandler, excluding the cover page.

    • visiblePageBinding

      public javafx.beans.binding.ObjectBinding<UIPage<?>> visiblePageBinding()
      Returns an ObjectBinding bound to the currently displayed page of this UIPageHandler.

      The visible page is determined by the following:

      1. If the page list is not empty, the last page in the page list is returned.
      2. If the page list is empty, the cover page is returned.
      Returns:
      An ObjectBinding bound to the currently displayed UIPage of this UIPageHandler.
      See Also:
      getVisiblePage()

    • getVisiblePage

      public UIPage<?> getVisiblePage()
      Returns the page currently being displayed by this UIPageHandler.

      The visible page is determined by the following:

      1. If the page list is not empty, the last page in the page list is returned.
      2. If the page list is empty, the cover page is returned.
      Returns:
      The UIPage currently being displayed by this UIPageHandler.
      See Also:
      visiblePageBinding()

    • hasPagedContentBinding

      public javafx.beans.binding.BooleanBinding hasPagedContentBinding()
      Returns a BooleanBinding that checks if this UIPageHandler has paged content.

      Paged content is defined as a page that is part of this UIPageHandler, but is not currently being displayed.
      The value of pageData.hasPagedContentBinding().get() will always be equal to getPages().isEmpty().

      Returns:
      A BooleanBinding that checks if this UIPageHandler has paged content.
      See Also:
      hasPagedContent()

    • hasPagedContent

      public boolean hasPagedContent()
      Returns true if this UIPageHandler has paged content, false if it does not.
      Returns:
      True if this UIPageHandler has paged content, false if it does not.
      See Also:
      hasPagedContentBinding()

    • containsPage

      public boolean containsPage​(UIPage<?> page)
      Checks if this UIPageHandler contains the specified page.

      A page is defined as being contained within a UIPageHandler if any of the following conditions are true:

      1. The page is contained within the page list.
      2. The page is the cover page.

      Synchronized.

      Parameters:
      page - The UIPage being searched for.
      Returns:
      True if this UIPageHandler contains the specified page, false otherwise.
      See Also:
      coverPageProperty(), getPages()

    • turnTo

      public void turnTo​(UIPage<?> page)
      Turns this UIPageHandler to the specified page.
      1. All pages that are after the specified page are removed from the page list.
      2. If the specified page is the cover page, the page list is cleared.
      3. If this UIPageHandler does not contain the specified page, turnToNew(UIPage) is called.

      Synchronized.

      Parameters:
      page - The UIPage being made the next page in the page list (that is, the page being turned to).
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - If the specified page is null.
      See Also:
      turnToNew(UIPage)

    • turnToNew

      public void turnToNew​(UIPage<?> page)
      Adds the specified page to this UIPageHandler, and then turns to that UIPageHandler.

      Unlike turnTo, this method throws an UnsupportedOperationException if this UIPageHandler already contains the specified page.

      Synchronized.

      Parameters:
      page - The UIPage being turned to.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - If the specified page is null.
      UnsupportedOperationException - If this UIPageHandler already contains the specified page (see containsPage).
      See Also:
      turnTo(UIPage)

    • back

      public void back()
      Turns this UIPageHandler back one page.

      Equivalent to getPages().pollLast().

      Synchronized.

      See Also:
      turnTo(UIPage), turnToNew(UIPage), backUnchecked()

    • backUnchecked

      public void backUnchecked()
      Turns this UIPageHandler back one page.

      Equivalent to getPages().getLast(). This method differs from back() only in that it throws an exception if the page list is empty.

      Synchronized.

      See Also:
      turnTo(UIPage), turnToNew(UIPage), back()

    • calcVisiblePage

      private UIPage<?> calcVisiblePage()
      Calculates the currently visible page.

      The visible page is determined by the following:

      1. If the page list is not empty, the last page in the page list is returned.
      2. If the page list is empty, the cover page is returned.

      Synchronized.

      Returns:
      The currently visible UIPage.
